<h2>1. BLACK DOMAIN</h2>
<div class="img-placeholder">🖼️ [GAMBAR: Lanskap Black Domain]</div>

<h3>I. Landscape & Geography</h3>
<p><strong>Location:</strong> Far western edge, bordered by Western Seam Zone to the east, Black Zone of the Western Sea to the west, Vorn Mountains to the north, and Southern Sea to the south.</p>
<p><strong>Area:</strong> 24 million km² — second largest territory, exceeded only by the Valdran Empire.</p>
<p><strong>Condition:</strong> A wasteland of barren black soil. The largest battlefield of the Primordial War. Zero natural resources, zero agriculture, no valuable minerals. Inhabitants survive almost entirely on harvested monster meat.</p>
<p><strong>Anomalies:</strong> A suffocating aura of death envelops the entire region. Phantom sounds of clashing weapons echo from the earth. The sky is eternally stained deep red or dark purple.</p>
<p><strong>Capital:</strong> Malakh-Kar — the silent fortress city where The First King slumbers in the deepest abyss.</p>

<h3>II. History</h3>
<p>The Black Domain was forged in the fires of <strong>The First Great War (1500–1715 EK)</strong>. The First King rallied the demon race and all the rejected ones of the world, launching a devastating campaign that nearly drove the other races to extinction.</p>
<p>The conquest was halted at the <strong>Battle of Malakh-Kar in 1715 EK</strong>. The First King fought seven legendary Heroes simultaneously, killing four, before collapsing into eternal slumber. Of the 12 Demon Commanders who clashed with the 7 Fallen Angels, only five survived: <em>The Unraveler, Vorlag, Kazagar, Gorath, and Zar'goth</em>. Three Fallen Angels fell.</p>
<p>Since that defeat, The Unraveler has appointed four new Commanders: <em>Alleen, Silphira, Vexia, and Nuva</em>. The domain is bound by a fanatical public doctrine: the stitched New World is a false prison that must be destroyed. Whether The Unraveler herself believes this is known only to one.</p>

<h3>III. Government & Power Structure</h3>
<p><strong>Form:</strong> Absolute Military Dictatorship.</p>
<p><strong>Apex Leader:</strong> The Unraveler — supreme Demon King, Weave Level 8–9. Unquestionable authority over all aspects of the domain.</p>
<p><strong>Eight Commanders:</strong> Weave Levels 6–8. Control military might, covert intelligence, and grand strategy. Hierarchy is a brutal meritocracy based on raw power and seniority.</p>
<p><strong>Hidden Faction:</strong> The Revisionist Faction — founded in absolute secrecy by Commander Vexia. Quietly questions the doctrine of eternal war. Discovery means certain death.</p>

<h3>IV. Key Characteristics</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Genetic Memory:</strong> Every demon is born with 5,000 years of accumulated combat knowledge. They know how to kill without being taught.</li>
  <li><strong>Old World Arsenal:</strong> 70% of original Old World weaponry remains functional — beam-lances, toxic-gas dispersers, mechanized golems.</li>
  <li><strong>Shadow Economy:</strong> Food imported via black markets. Payment: illegally exported ancient weapons and dark magic to rogue factions like the Iron Covenant.</li>
  <li><strong>Demographics:</strong> Almost exclusively Pure Demon. A sparse few loyal — or tragically oppressed — members of other races exist at the margins.</li>
</ul>

<h3>V. Daily Life & Technology</h3>
<p><strong>Infrastructure:</strong> No paved roads. Only shattered remnants of Old World routes, barely maintained. Travel is a test of endurance and will.</p>
<p><strong>Transportation:</strong> Commanders and elite forces ride tamed war-beasts — predators twisted by Aether and Old World exposure. No Aether-wagons. Speed and ferocity replace comfort.</p>
<p><strong>Sustenance:</strong> Low-grade Aether Cores from the Western Seam Zone power the forges of Malakh-Kar. Food is exclusively monster meat, strictly rationed. No farms. No grain silos. Every meal is a reminder of what the domain has lost.</p>
